00:22:46,847 --> 00:22:50,847
載せず鍵かけておこう ＃％＆＄”＝〜 ほにゃららむにゃらこぽんぽこ
Let's keep it locked up, #%&$~ gibberish.

349
00:22:50,847 --> 00:22:53,347
ほらね、聴き取れない!!
See? You can't hear it!

350
00:22:53,347 --> 00:22:56,647
皆いつもくよくよ悩み
Everyone is always worrying,

351
00:22:56,647 --> 00:22:59,747
締め切りに追われ歴史を作り
chased by deadlines, making history,

352
00:22:59,747 --> 00:23:02,547
弱さを無理やりごまかし
forcibly cheating our weakness.

353
00:23:02,547 --> 00:23:05,747
君の芝生は緑 青じゃなくていい
Your lawn is green, it doesn't have to be blue.

354
00:23:05,747 --> 00:23:09,147
アイドル撮られちゃった真冬の空に
The idol got photographed in the midwinter sky,

355
00:23:09,147 --> 00:23:12,447
政治家ぶれてブレちゃった帰り道
and the politician shook and faltered on the way home,

356
00:23:12,447 --> 00:23:15,547
とうちゃんローン組んだみはてぬ先
Dad took out a loan for an endless future.

357
00:23:15,547 --> 00:23:18,447
でも時は全部を流して
But time washes everything away.

358
00:23:18,447 --> 00:23:22,047
人はこれって時にどうしても
I wonder why people always say,

359
00:23:22,047 --> 00:23:24,447
「時間を戻せたら」とかいうね
"if only we could turn back the hands of time..."

360
00:23:24,447 --> 00:23:27,747
残誰も直せないよ 治せないんだな
yet it's impossible and it always has been.

361
00:23:27,747 --> 00:23:31,047
昔からそうだし まぁしょうがないね
Life can get tough, so we might as well enjoy it.

362
00:23:31,047 --> 00:23:34,247
きっと先は深くて不安定
The future is surely deep and unstable,

363
00:23:34,247 --> 00:23:37,447
でも お行儀よくちゃつまんないね
but being well-behaved is so boring.

364
00:23:37,447 --> 00:23:40,447
タイムマシーンに乗り込んで
So let's hop in a time machine

365
00:23:40,447 --> 00:23:43,547
トラベラーになれたら
and become a traveler.

366
00:23:43,547 --> 00:23:46,847
俺ってやつはいつも気づいた時は手遅れ
A guy like me is always too late when he realizes,

367
00:23:46,847 --> 00:23:50,047
絵空事ばかりうつつ抜かして
losing myself in nothing but fantasies,

368
00:23:50,047 --> 00:23:53,047
大事な人すら救えない
unable to save even the people who matter.

369
00:23:53,047 --> 00:23:56,247
だからこんな歌で自分に言い聞かして
So I tell myself with a song like this.

370
00:23:56,247 --> 00:24:00,047
あの時 あいつは多分 気を使って
Back then, he was probably being considerate,

371
00:24:00,047 --> 00:24:03,047
とくに顔色変えず 何もないふり
not changing his expression, pretending nothing happened.

372
00:24:03,047 --> 00:24:05,747
なんで言わないんだって ムカついてもね
Even if I get annoyed wondering why he didn't say anything,

373
00:24:05,747 --> 00:24:09,147
やさしさからきてたなら しょうがないね
if it came from kindness, it can't be helped.

374
00:24:09,147 --> 00:24:12,147
願わくばディスコで親父と母さんが会った日に行きたいね
Hopefully, I want to go to the day my
dad and mom met at a disco.

375
00:24:12,147 --> 00:24:15,347
後ろのジョックスに酒 かけて息子じきじきにチャンス作ってやるぜ
I'll pour alcohol on the jocks in the back
and make a chance myself as their son.

376
00:24:15,347 --> 00:24:21,547
どんなでかい時計だってすべてさ 始まりはこんな小さい歯車
No matter how huge a clock is, everything starts
with such a small gear.

377
00:24:21,547 --> 00:24:28,147
細かいことはもういいや 疲れた
I'm done with the details, I'm tired.

378
00:24:28,147 --> 00:24:31,047
別に怒ってないってさ未来は
The future says it's not particularly mad at me.

379
00:24:45,847 --> 00:24:49,047
人はこれって時にどうしても
I wonder why people always say,

380
00:24:49,047 --> 00:24:52,047
「時間を戻せたら」とかいうね
"if only we could turn back the hands of time..."

381
00:24:52,047 --> 00:24:55,247
でも誰も直せないよ 治せないんだな
yet it's impossible and it always has been.

382
00:24:55,247 --> 00:25:00,047
昔からそうだし まぁしょうがないね
Life can get tough, so we might as well enjoy it.

383
00:25:00,095 --> 00:25:02,595
きっと先は深くて不安定
I'm sure the path ahead is deep and unstable,

384
00:25:02,595 --> 00:25:05,895
でもお行儀良くちゃつまんないね
but playing by the rules is just boring.

385
00:25:05,895 --> 00:25:08,895
タイムマシンに乗り込んで
Hop on the time machine

386
00:25:08,895 --> 00:25:11,895
トラベラーになれたら
and if we could become travelers...

387
00:25:24,995 --> 00:25:25,895
Done

388
00:25:58,095 --> 00:26:00,295
yo シボレーのドアを蹴り開けて
Yo, kicking open the Chevrolet door,

389
00:26:00,295 --> 00:26:02,995
街に飛び出した俺たち
we leaped out into the city streets.

390
00:26:02,995 --> 00:26:05,195
暴力 酒に女 音楽
Violence, alcohol, women, music...

391
00:26:05,195 --> 00:26:07,795
中指立てる大人の仮面に
flipping the bird to the masks of adults.

392
00:26:07,795 --> 00:26:10,095
Oh さぁ踊ろう 「今日」という日を
Oh, come on, let's dance, taking "today"...

393
00:26:10,095 --> 00:26:12,295
生き急ぐメンバー
...with the crew living life in the fast lane.

394
00:26:12,295 --> 00:26:14,495
足りねぇか？ Little louder!
Not enough? Little louder!

395
00:26:14,495 --> 00:26:17,395
欲望渦巻く路上が現場
The desire-swirling streets are our stage.

396
00:26:17,395 --> 00:26:19,895
Yeah いつだってそうだろう？
Yeah, it's always been that way, right?

397
00:26:19,895 --> 00:26:22,095
ブルハ 尾崎 永ちゃんが教科書
The Blue Hearts, Ozaki, and Yazawa were our textbooks.

398
00:26:22,095 --> 00:26:24,495
くたばるまで格好つけてぇ
We wanna look cool until the day we die.

399
00:26:24,495 --> 00:26:26,595
誓ったよあの放課後
We made that vow after school.

400
00:26:26,595 --> 00:26:28,895
俺らピーターパン
We are Peter Pans.

401
00:26:28,895 --> 00:26:31,095
「またいつか」なんて言っちゃいかん
We can't just say "maybe someday."

402
00:26:31,095 --> 00:26:33,495
嘲笑っとる大人に言ってやるぁ
We'll show those sneering adults

403
00:26:33,495 --> 00:26:35,895
人生はたったの一回だ
that you only get one shot at life.

404
00:26:36,595 --> 00:26:40,095
胸の奥底 初期衝動
Deep in our hearts, that primal urge...

405
00:26:40,495 --> 00:26:44,895
見て見ぬフリ No, No
...we won't turn a blind eye, no, no.

406
00:26:44,895 --> 00:26:46,895
夢追い笑われ
Mocked for chasing dreams,

407
00:26:46,895 --> 00:26:48,895
傷だらけでギラつく My way
covered in scars, shining on my way.

408
00:26:48,895 --> 00:26:50,895
Go on! You should know

409
00:26:50,895 --> 00:26:52,995
who we are

410
00:26:52,995 --> 00:26:54,895
Forever Young

411
00:26:54,895 --> 00:26:57,095
Hey! Just next to me from now

412
00:26:57,095 --> 00:26:59,895
大切なことは
What matters most...

413
00:26:59,895 --> 00:27:02,095
魂の状態
...is the state of your soul.

414
00:27:02,095 --> 00:27:03,995
Forever Young

415
00:27:03,995 --> 00:27:06,895
Hey! It's your turn next time from here

416
00:27:06,895 --> 00:27:09,195
「あの日始めれば良かった」
"I wish I had started that day."

417
00:27:09,195 --> 00:27:11,295
その次の
The next best time...

418
00:27:11,295 --> 00:27:13,495
始めるべき時は今
...to start is right now!

419
00:27:13,495 --> 00:27:16,095
高笑いする都会の喧騒
The roaring laughter of the city's bustle,

420
00:27:16,095 --> 00:27:18,295
ウケ狙いならば振り向けんぞ
if you're just seeking attention, I won't look back.

421
00:27:18,295 --> 00:27:20,395
何連呼？ 忘れろ？ 夢流した便所
Repeating what? Forget it? The toilet where dreams were flushed,

422
00:27:20,395 --> 00:27:22,995
見下ろしてきやがる摩天楼
with skyscrapers looking down on us.

423
00:27:22,995 --> 00:27:25,295
Oh まるで勝新みたく破天荒
Oh, wild and reckless like Shintaro Katsu,

424
00:27:25,295 --> 00:27:27,595
伝説へとアテンド
attending to our legendary path.

425
00:27:27,595 --> 00:27:29,895
怖にゃあ怖にゃあってその程度
Cowering "I'm scared, I'm scared" — is that all you've got?

426
00:27:29,895 --> 00:27:32,195
捨てろ負け惜しみ 過去の栄光
Throw away your sour grapes and past glory.

427
00:27:32,195 --> 00:27:34,295
永遠なんぞはねぇて
There is no such thing as eternity,

428
00:27:34,295 --> 00:27:36,595
いつか天へ召され
one day we'll be called to heaven.

429
00:27:36,595 --> 00:27:39,195
ペンの書き殴ったこの魂は2PACみたく
This soul scribbled in pen, like 2Pac's,

430
00:27:39,195 --> 00:27:41,395
誰かの心を通過
will pass through someone's heart.

431
00:27:41,395 --> 00:27:43,995
なぁ 何か忘れちゃねぇか
Hey, haven't we forgotten something?

432
00:27:43,995 --> 00:27:46,395
人生まるで映画 皆がエンターテイナー
Life is like a movie, everyone's an entertainer.

433
00:27:46,395 --> 00:27:48,895
思い出せ思想は現実化する
Remember, thoughts manifest into reality.

434
00:27:48,895 --> 00:27:51,195
誰がHighway飛ばすBentayga
Who's speeding down the highway in a Bentayga?

435
00:27:51,895 --> 00:27:55,295
胸の奥底 初期衝動
Deep in our hearts, that primal urge...

436
00:27:55,895 --> 00:28:00,095
見て見ぬフリ No, No
...we won't turn a blind eye, no, no.

437
00:28:00,095 --> 00:28:02,195
夢追い笑われ
Mocked for chasing dreams,

438
00:28:02,195 --> 00:28:04,195
傷だらけでギラつく My way
covered in scars, shining on my way.

439
00:28:04,195 --> 00:28:06,095
Go on! You should know

440
00:28:06,095 --> 00:28:08,195
who we are

441
00:28:08,195 --> 00:28:10,095
Forever Young

442
00:28:10,095 --> 00:28:13,195
Hey! 俺たちは今日だって
Hey! Even today, we are...

443
00:28:13,195 --> 00:28:15,195
若気の至りのような
...still chasing dreams

444
00:28:15,195 --> 00:28:17,395
夢を追いかけて来た
like the folly of youth.

445
00:28:17,395 --> 00:28:19,495
Forever Young

446
00:28:19,495 --> 00:28:22,095
Hey! 変わるはずなんてない
Hey! There's no way we're changing.

447
00:28:22,095 --> 00:28:24,095
さぁ至ってやろうぜ！
Come on, let's reach the top!

448
00:28:24,095 --> 00:28:26,195
今日は残された人生で
Today is, of the life we have left...

449
00:28:26,195 --> 00:28:28,095
一番若い日だろ
...the youngest day, isn't it?

450
00:28:28,095 --> 00:28:31,095
半端な覚悟ならドブに捨てな
If your resolve is half-hearted, throw it in the gutter!

451
00:28:32,495 --> 00:28:34,695
往生際が悪いテメー笑い飛ばし
Laughing off your bad grace,

452
00:28:34,695 --> 00:28:36,995
誇れ Better days
take pride in better days!

453
00:28:36,995 --> 00:28:38,795
まだ終わらない
It's not over yet,

454
00:28:38,795 --> 00:28:40,895
終わらせやしない 燃え尽きるまで保存
we won't let it end until we burn out!

455
00:28:42,595 --> 00:28:44,295
まだ終わらない保存
It's not over yet,

456
00:28:44,295 --> 00:28:46,095
終わらせやしない くたばるまで保存
we won't let it end until we die!

457
00:28:48,095 --> 00:28:49,995
Forever Young

458
00:28:49,995 --> 00:28:52,995
もう夢を追いかけ本気になった心は
A heart that got serious about chasing dreams...

459
00:28:52,995 --> 00:28:56,895
自分の指図も受けない
...won't even take orders from itself.保存

460
00:28:56,895 --> 00:28:59,095
Forever Young

461
00:28:59,095 --> 00:29:02,195
Hey! その思いから逃れられないなら
Hey! If you can't escape those feelings...保存

462
00:29:02,195 --> 00:29:08,095
自ら向かうだけ
...then just face them yourself.

463
00:29:08,895 --> 00:29:11,195
終わらせやしない
We won't let it end,

464
00:29:11,195 --> 00:29:12,895
燃え尽きるまで
until we burn out!

465
00:29:12,895 --> 00:29:14,295
まだ終わらない
It's not over yet,

466
00:29:14,295 --> 00:29:16,295
終わらせやしない くたばるまで
we won't let it end until we die!

467
00:29:16,295 --> 00:29:19,895
まだ終わらない まだ終わらない
It's not over yet, it's not over yet...

468
00:29:19,895 --> 00:29:21,895
Forever Young

469
00:29:21,895 --> 00:29:24,095
そう今日という日は
Yes, today is...

470
00:29:24,095 --> 00:29:28,095
お前に残された人生の一番若い日
...the youngest day of the rest of your life.

471
00:29:36,595 --> 00:29:40,095
マリン、来てくれてありがとう！
Marine, thank you so much for coming!

472
00:29:40,095 --> 00:29:43,095
呼んでくれてありがとう！
Thank you for inviting me!

473
00:29:43,095 --> 00:29:48,095
いや、マジこの「Forever Young」って曲をマリンと一緒に歌いたかったの！「Forever Young」って曲をね。
No, really, I seriously wanted to sing this song "Forever Young" with Marine!

474
00:29:48,095 --> 00:29:52,095
ああ、それはマリンがおばさんにならないように？
Ah, is that so Marine doesn't become an old lady?

475
00:29:52,095 --> 00:29:55,095
そう！もうフォーエバーのヤングでいようねっていうね！
Exactly! Like, "let's stay forever young," you know!

476
00:29:55,095 --> 00:29:59,095
そうだね、永遠にヤングでいましょう、みんな、みんな、フォーエバーヤングで！
That's right, let's stay forever young, everyone!

477
00:30:00,070 --> 00:30:01,370
悩んだー！
I was torn!

478
00:30:01,370 --> 00:30:02,870
でもマリン今日はね、今日はね
But Marine today, you know, today...

479
00:30:02,870 --> 00:30:05,470
え、後ろ見て？
Wait, look behind you.

480
00:30:05,470 --> 00:30:08,070
演奏してくれてる...
They are performing...

481
00:30:08,070 --> 00:30:09,570
気まずいよ
This is awkward.

482
00:30:09,570 --> 00:30:11,870
今日はね、演奏してくれてるの、みんなが
Today, they're performing for us, everyone!

483
00:30:11,870 --> 00:30:13,570
乗ってるよ、乗ってるよ
They're grooving, they're grooving!

484
00:30:13,570 --> 00:30:15,070
乗ってるでしょ？ え、どの人と写真撮りたい？
They're grooving, right? Wait, who do you want to take a picture with?

485
00:30:15,070 --> 00:30:17,070
え、そんな、一人だけみたいな、そんな...
Wait, just one person... that's like...

486
00:30:17,070 --> 00:30:19,470
いやいや、二人選んでいい、二人選んでいい
No, no, you can choose two! You can choose two.

487
00:30:19,470 --> 00:30:21,570
かわいそうじゃん、選ばれなかった人
That's so sad for the one who doesn't get chosen.

488
00:30:21,570 --> 00:30:23,070
二人選ぼう、二人
Let's choose two, two of them!

489
00:30:23,070 --> 00:30:25,070
俺もう、ころねすきがなんか...
I feel like the Koronesuki is...

490
00:30:25,070 --> 00:30:27,070
いいよ、マリンが選ぶんだよ！
It's okay, Marine will choose!

491
00:30:27,070 --> 00:30:28,270
あ、マリンが選ぶ...
Oh, Marine will choose...

492
00:30:28,270 --> 00:30:30,270
そう、最初は... / 待って、あ、待って、映して後ろ
Yes, first up is... / Wait, show the ones behind us.

493
00:30:30,270 --> 00:30:33,270
みんな下向いて
Everyone is looking down!

494
00:30:38,270 --> 00:30:41,070
細犬さん！
Hosoinu-san!

495
00:30:41,070 --> 00:30:44,270
かわいい！
So cute!

496
00:30:44,270 --> 00:30:48,070
じゃあ、細犬と、まず、まず写真撮ろうか！ / かわいいよ、細犬
Then let's take a picture with Hosoinu first! / Hosoinu is cute.

497
00:30:48,070 --> 00:30:51,270
こっちおいで、マリン、こっちにね / はい、細犬です！
Come here, Marine, to this side. / Yes, here is Hosoinu!

498
00:30:51,270 --> 00:30:54,070
えっと、細犬はギターかな？
So, is Hosoinu on guitar?

499
00:30:54,070 --> 00:30:56,570
ギターですか？細犬ちゃん
Are you on guitar, Hosoinu-chan?

500
00:30:56,570 --> 00:30:58,270
ベロの色が... / かわいいね
His tongue color is... / It's cute.

501
00:30:58,270 --> 00:31:00,070
乾いてる、ベロ / ベロ乾いて、澄んでるんだけど
His tongue is dry. / His tongue is dry, but it looks clear...

502
00:31:00,070 --> 00:31:02,570
かわいい / 乾いてるから触らないでね
Cute. / It's dry so don't touch it!

503
00:31:02,570 --> 00:31:05,070
ごめんね、いっぱい触って
Sorry for touching you so much.

504
00:31:05,070 --> 00:31:07,570
え、次、誰がいい？ / かわいい、あと一人、あと一人
So, who's next? / Cute, one more, one more.

505
00:31:07,570 --> 00:31:09,570
じゃあ...
Then...

506
00:31:09,570 --> 00:31:11,270
太犬？ / 太犬 / 太犬だね
Futoinu? / Futoinu. / Futoinu, right.

507
00:31:11,270 --> 00:31:15,070
はい、太犬はドラムです！かわいい！ / でかい！
Yes, Futoinu is on drums! So cute! / Huge!

508
00:31:15,070 --> 00:31:18,070
かわいいね
So cute.

509
00:31:18,070 --> 00:31:21,070
ベロの色がちょっと明るい
His tongue color is a bit brighter.

510
00:31:21,070 --> 00:31:24,070
細犬より
Compared to Hosoinu's.

511
00:31:24,070 --> 00:31:26,570
撮った？ / みんな撮った？ / 撮った？
Did you take it? / Did everyone get a picture? / Did you?

512
00:31:26,570 --> 00:31:30,070
かわいい！ / オッケーだね / うん、オッケー
So cute! / We're good, right? / Yeah, okay.

513
00:31:30,070 --> 00:31:33,070
え、じゃあ最後さ、二人とも撮ろうよ！二人でも！
Then, let's take a picture of both of us at the end! With both!

514
00:31:33,070 --> 00:31:35,070
あ、そうだね、二人でも撮ろう、二人で
Oh, that's right. Let's take one with both of us.

515
00:31:35,070 --> 00:31:38,270
二人で撮って
Take a picture of the two of us.

516
00:31:38,270 --> 00:31:41,270
え？ちょっと...
Wait, what...?

517
00:31:41,270 --> 00:31:45,070
あ、ごめんごめん！やっぱりじゃあね、やっぱり一人で撮りたいみたいだから
Ah, sorry, sorry! It seems they want to take individual pictures after all.

518
00:31:45,070 --> 00:31:47,070
あ、やっぱりね！ころねすきーだもんね
Oh, of course! Since they're Koronesuki.

519
00:31:47,070 --> 00:31:50,070
撮りましょうか / ころねすきー、ころさん好き？
Shall we take it? / Koronesuki, do you like Koro-san?

520
00:31:50,070 --> 00:31:53,070
好き？ころさん好き？
Do you like me? Do you like Koro-san?

521
00:31:53,070 --> 00:31:57,070
あ、よかった。え、マリンも好き？ / 間に入ろう
Ah, thank goodness. Wait, do you like Marine too? / Let's get in the middle.

522
00:31:57,070 --> 00:31:59,070
なんでだよ！ / ころねすきーなのに、ころさんの隣に立てない気分どう？
Why?! / Even though you're a Koronesuki, how does it feel to not be able to stand next to Koro-san?

523
00:31:59,070 --> 00:32:04,070
嬉しい？マリンが隣で
Are you happy Marine is next to you?

524
00:32:04,070 --> 00:32:06,070
嬉しくない... / 本当は好きなんでしょ？
Not happy... / You actually like her, don't you?

525
00:32:06,070 --> 00:32:09,070
やめろ！やめろよ！ / ダメ、もうダメ、帰るよ、帰るよもう
Stop it! Stop it! / No, no more, I'm going home, I'm going home now.

526
00:32:09,070 --> 00:32:11,070
はい、帰ろう。はい、帰ろう
Okay, let's go. Yes, let's go back.

527
00:32:11,070 --> 00:32:14,070
はい、今日はね、今日のバンドメンバーがいましたけれどですね / ええ
Yes, so we had today's band members here today, but... / Yeah.

528
00:32:14,070 --> 00:32:17,070
はい、あ、マリンとも最後撮りたい / あ、とろとろ、とろー
Oh, I want to take a final photo with Marine too. / Let's take it, let's take it.

529
00:32:17,070 --> 00:32:21,070
せっかくだね、Forever Youngだから今日は
Since we're Forever Young today, after all.

530
00:32:21,070 --> 00:32:24,070
マイク！マイク間違えちゃってるけど / マイクね、うん、いいよいいよ
The mic! You got the mic wrong, but... / The mic, yeah, it's fine, it's fine.

531
00:32:24,070 --> 00:32:28,070
でかい声で喋るな、拾うから！
Don't speak in a loud voice, it'll pick it up!

532
00:32:30,070 --> 00:32:33,070
取れた？
Did you get it?

533
00:32:33,070 --> 00:32:35,070
いけてる？ / 太犬！
Is it good? / Futoinu!

534
00:32:35,070 --> 00:32:37,070
いい感じに撮れたね
We got a good one, right?

535
00:32:37,070 --> 00:32:40,070
ありがとう、マリン！ / ありがとう
Thank you, Marine! / Thank you.

536
00:32:40,070 --> 00:32:45,070
ね、ちょっと次の曲があるから行くけど / 次の曲。一人で帰れる？
Hey, I have to go because the next song is starting... / Next song. Can you go back alone?

537
00:32:45,070 --> 00:32:48,070
あ、うん、大丈夫、大丈夫、大丈夫 / じゃあ...
Oh, yeah, I'm fine, I'm fine. / Then...

538
00:32:48,070 --> 00:32:51,070
バンドメンバーのことよろしく / え？じゃあマリン、バイバイ！
Take care of the band members. / Eh? Okay, Marine, bye-bye!

539
00:32:51,070 --> 00:32:54,070
よろしくって何よ、よろしく...
What do you mean by "take care"...

540
00:32:54,070 --> 00:32:58,070
どんな曲？あ、え？みんな次の曲だよ！
What kind of song? Oh, everyone, it's the next song!

541
00:33:01,070 --> 00:33:07,570
らららーらーらー おおー
La la la la la...

542
00:33:07,570 --> 00:33:13,070
サボり方とか甘え方とか 逃げ方とか言い訳の仕方とか
How to slack off, how to be spoiled,
how to run away, how to make excuses,

543
00:33:13,070 --> 00:33:19,070
やっと覚えてきた 身につけてきた 柔らかい頭
I just finally learned it all, it's imprinted on my head.
This is some flexible mind.

544
00:33:19,070 --> 00:33:24,070
カッコのつけ方 調子のこき方 腹の据え方 良い年のこき方
How to look cool, how to be cocky,
how to chill out, how to age well,

545
00:33:24,070 --> 00:33:30,070
脂の乗りに乗った 濁った目をした だらしない体
now I'm nailing it all, but my eyes are dead.
This is some sloppy body.

546
00:33:30,070 --> 00:33:35,270
嫌われ方や 慕われ方や 叱り方とか 綺麗なぶつかり方
How to be hated, how to be idolized,
how to tell off others, how to elegantly explain myself.

547
00:33:35,270 --> 00:33:39,570
もっと覚えたいことが 山のようにある
There is so much we still wanna learn.

548
00:33:39,570 --> 00:33:41,270
のびしろしかないわ
We've got nothing but potential!

549
00:33:41,270 --> 00:33:43,070
のびしろしかないわ
We've got nothing but potential!

550
00:33:43,070 --> 00:33:46,070
のびしろしかないわ
We've got nothing but potential!

551
00:33:46,070 --> 00:33:49,070
のびしろしかないわ
We've got nothing but potential!

552
00:33:49,070 --> 00:33:52,070
俺らまだのびしろしかないわ
We've still got nothing but potential!

553
00:33:52,070 --> 00:33:54,570
悪者扱い して来た街で
In the city I used to demonize,

554
00:33:54,570 --> 00:33:57,070
悪者扱い して来た大人へ
I turn into the adult I used to demonize.

555
00:33:57,070 --> 00:34:00,070
変わりゆく俺 鏡の中へ
If I question my ever-changing self inside the mirror,

556
00:34:00,070 --> 00:34:03,070
尋ねても答えは yeah yeah yeah yeah
the answer is always yeah, yeah, yeah, yeah.

557
00:34:03,070 --> 00:34:05,570
去る者は追わない 引く手は引いて
I won't run after the past, I'll retreat when necessary,

558
00:34:05,570 --> 00:34:08,570
丸く収めた 軽くあしらって
I'll wrap up smoothly, I'll dodge and weave.

559
00:34:08,570 --> 00:34:11,070
鏡の中で嘲笑ってるお前
And to you who's laughing through the mirror,

560
00:34:11,070 --> 00:34:14,070
括れやしなかった たったの三文字で
I say I didn't sum people up to a single word!

561
00:34:14,070 --> 00:34:19,570
日々重くなる足取りで 自分の歩幅で闊歩してる
Recently my stride's getting heavy,
still I'll be swaggering around on my pace.

562
00:34:19,570 --> 00:34:21,870
カマす時ゃカマす 負かす時ゃ負かす / 割と適当な段取りで
I'll do it when I do it! I'll lose when I lose!
I'll go with this careless plan!

563
00:34:25,070 --> 00:34:27,570
やっと分かって来たかも
I think I finally figured it out,

564
00:34:27,570 --> 00:34:30,070
このポンコツの操縦の仕方
how to steer this piece of junk.

565
00:34:30,070 --> 00:34:35,570
19の時の ついに来た感より もっとすがすがしい気持ち
